<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="MTA20">
<l>peṟṟār taḷaikaḻalap pērntōr kuṟaḷuruvāyc</l>
<l>ceṟṟār paṭikaṭanta ceṅkaṇmā – ṉaṟṟā</l>
<l>maraimalarc cēvaṭiyai vāṉavarkai kūppi</l>
<l>niraimalarkoṇ ṭēttuvarā ṉiṉṟu</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Having returned so that the bonds of those who begot [him] loosened<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">This verse is elliptical in detail, but clearly implies more than one incarnation. The first phrase refers to the parents of Kṛṣṇa who were imprisoned by Kaṃsa, but the second phrase includes an unequivocal reference to the Vāmana incarnation.</note>, in the form</l>
<l>of a dwarf, red-eyed Māl who crossed the earth of the enemy<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">ceṟṟār here must refer to Māvali, with a honorific for the sake of etukai.</note>,</l>
<l>folding hands before [his] good lotus-flower red feet the celestials</l>
<l>praise steadily with blossoms in rows.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
